   321→
   322→  <!-- NEW FINDINGS -->
   323→  <div class="cycle-box-new" style="margin-top: 40px;">
   324→    <h3>Cycle 6 — New Finding: BC Spring Break Ends on March 27</h3>
   325→    <ul>
   326→      <li><strong>Found:</strong> Vancouver School District (VSB) spring break runs March 16–27, 2026. March 13 is the last school day before break; March 30 is the first day back. This means March 27 is the final Friday of spring break — a detail absent from all six prior cycles of research.</li>
   327→      <li><strong>Impact on guests:</strong> Some group members may have been traveling during the break and returning that day. Factor in potential headcount volatility. The organizer's March 25 headcount confirmation call is more important than on a typical Friday, given spring break travel disruptions.</li>
   328→      <li><strong>Impact on venues:</strong> Vancouver restaurants are measurably busier during spring break than a typical mid-March Friday. Combined with the Auto Show and Blossoms After Dark, March 27 is the most event-dense evening of the three-week period since the Auto Show opened. Anyone walk-in planning to eat out that evening will find the city busier than usual — but the group has (or should have) a reservation, making this a non-issue if booked.</li>
   329→      <li><strong>Impact on parking / transit:</strong> Spring break families are a significant portion of the Auto Show's attendance. The 9 PM Waterfront Station exit crowd documented in Cycle 5 is likely larger than a typical spring Auto Show Friday. This reinforces the "board before 9 PM or wait until 9:45 PM" guidance already in the action guide.</li>
   330→      <li><strong>Action required:</strong> Add one sentence to the action guide noting March 27 is the last day of spring break — primarily as context for why the March 25 headcount confirmation is extra-critical. The dinner-brief guest card does not need updating for this (it's an organizer consideration, not a guest-facing note).</li>
   331→    </ul>
   332→  </div>
   333→
   334→  <!-- RESOLVED GAP -->
   335→  <div class="cycle-box-resolved">
   336→    <h3>Cycle 6 — Gap Resolved: Torafuku Group Booking Policy Confirmed</h3>
   337→    <ul>
   338→      <li><strong>Resolved:</strong> Since Cycle 5, the action guide flagged Torafuku's group reservation policy as "not directly confirmed." It is now confirmed via the restaurant's own reservation page and third-party sources.</li>
   339→      <li><strong>Policy:</strong> Groups of 7 or more are booked by phone (778-903-2006) or email (letseat@torafuku.ca). A credit card hold may be required depending on party size and booking timing. The table is held for 2.5 hours for groups of 7+. A seasonal group tasting menu is available.</li>
   340→      <li><strong>Booking platform:</strong> Standard reservations (under 7 people) use OpenTable. Torafuku is also on Tock (exploretock.com/torafuku), which appears to be used for specific dining experiences. For a group of 8–10, the phone/email path is the correct one regardless.</li>
   341→      <li><strong>Action required:</strong> The actionguide's Torafuku section should be updated from the "call to confirm group policy" warning to the confirmed policy details. This eliminates the last outstanding gap identified in Cycle 5.</li>
   342→    </ul>
   343→  </div>
   344→
   345→  <!-- CYCLE HISTORY -->
   346→  <div class="cycle-hist">
   347→    <h3>Cumulative Correction History — All 6 Cycles</h3>
   348→    <ul>
   349→      <li><strong>Cycle 1:</strong> Initial research. Brix &amp; Mortar "Night in New Orleans" event fabricated. MeeT Gastown still listed as open.</li>
   350→      <li><strong>Cycle 2:</strong> Brix &amp; Mortar event removed. MeeT Gastown confirmed closed November 2025. Torafuku added. Brix &amp; Mortar address error introduced (wrong street).</li>
   351→      <li><strong>Cycle 3:</strong> Brix &amp; Mortar address corrected (1137 Hamilton St). MeeT halal nuance added. Parking estimate updated to $15–25+. research.html still showed Cycle 1 errors.</li>
   352→      <li><strong>Cycle 4:</strong> Full action guide rewrite. Online booking platforms confirmed. "No special events on March 27" stated — incorrect.</li>
   353→      <li><strong>Cycle 5:</strong> Three concurrent March 27 events discovered (Auto Show, Blossoms After Dark, Monster Jam). Auto Show transit timing documented. Torafuku group policy flagged as unconfirmed gap. Homer Street private room capacity confirmed (up to 12 private / up to 18 semi-private).</li>
   354→      <li><strong>Cycle 6 (this cycle):</strong> BC Spring Break ends March 27 — new finding. Torafuku group policy confirmed (7+, phone/email, CC hold may apply, 2.5 hours, seasonal group tasting menu). Minor concerts on March 27 found — city-wide, low venue impact. Canucks data conflict identified and resolved (no home game March 27 confirmed). Score raised from 89 to 91 as the outstanding Torafuku gap is now closed.</li>
   355→    </ul>
